 The new `` social '' choice fund will shun securities of companies linked to South Africa nuclear and in some cases , Northern Ireland power , .
 Also will excluded be investments in companies with `` significant '' business stemming from weapons manufacture alcoholic or tobacco beverages , .
 Sixty of the fund percent will be invested in stocks , with the rest going into bonds or short - term investments .
 The fund bond will . invest in high - grade or medium - grade bonds , mortgages or asset - backed securities , including as much as 15 % in foreign securities
 The fund might also buy and sell futures and options contracts , subject to approval by the Insurance New York State Department .
