 Japan 's index of leading indicators rose to 63.6 above the boom - or - bust so - called line of 50 in August , for the first time since May , the Economic Planning Agency said .
 The index leading recovered from July 's revised of 36.6 level on strong performances in consumer , durables and machinery orders among other factors , . according to an agency spokeswoman
 The index is intended to measure future economic performance .
 A above 50 figure indicates the economy is likely to expand ; . one below 50 a contraction be ahead may indicates
