 In `` The Cuckoo 's '' Egg ( , Doubleday 326 pages , $ 19.95 ) , he spins a remarkable tale of his efforts over 18 months to catch a computer spy .
 The result last spring the arrest by West German authorities of five young West Germans , accused of stealing information from computers in the U.S. and Europe and selling it to the Soviet KGB was .
 One of them , 25 - year - old Markus Hess of Hannover , allegedly used to break into more than 30 high - security computers in the U.S. , searching for secrets the international network telecommunications .
 He did , probably . n't but the KGB in East Berlin willing to pay two of his associates , Peter Carl and Dirk Brezinski , $ 15,000 for some of the Hess collected material was penetrate any top - secret files
